":"Good social-emotional skills are vital for children to be able to develop important skills such as cooperation, following directions, demonstrating self-control, and working well with others. As you introduce how things move, have children talk to their peers and demonstrate various movements together as they learn about them. "}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"day_2","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"week","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header_all-caps","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"LET’S INVESTIGATE"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_header_separator","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"|"}]},{"type":"text","text":"  WEEK 4: Make It Move"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"circle-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_2","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Share the Mind Builder: Make Connections "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Discuss with children how we can look at the connections between pushing and pulling things and how they move. "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"If we push something, it will move away from us. If we pull it, it will move closer to us. What is the connection between the wind blowing and leaves on a tree moving? Will the branches and leaves move faster or slower when the wind is stronger?"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_2","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Focus on Vocabulary"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Introduce new vocabulary. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"t